\>What \c[4]Equip Plugins\c[0] would you like to learn about?\<
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Equip Core\c[0] plugins makes quite a few changes for your projects. It affects the equip menu, equipment type handling, equipment rulings, and parameter control.
<WordWrap>This plugin enables your player to be able to switch out an actor’s equips mid-battle.
<WordWrap>This will take the player to the Equip menu rather than leave the player inside the battle scene.

<WordWrap>Games that use the \c[4]YEP_X_ItemUpgradeSlots\c[0], \c[4]YEP_X_ItemDurability\c[0], and \c[4]YEP_X_AttachAugment\c[0] plugins may notice that it's not too intuitive to modify items from the item menu when they're equipped to the actors in the equip menu.
<WordWrap>This plugin will add a "Customize" option to the Equip menu that will function as a shortcut to the Item menu for quick customization access.
<WordWrap>Place restrictions on when an actor can equip a weapon or piece of armor. Set level requirements, stat requirements, switch requirements, and more.
<WordWrap>This plugin will also provide a separate equipment requirement window to show the player what is needed in order for gear to be equipped.
<WordWrap>Ever wanted to give your swords different images despite being the same sword type? Or how about your axes? Or any weapon?
<WordWrap>Now you can! On top of that, you can even use custom images to accomplish this.

<WordWrap>This plugin allows your game to be able to replace the \c[4]Attack\c[0] and \c[4]Guard\c[0] commands or give them the option of having a skill randomly occur when using them in reference to \c[4]Golden Sun\c[0]'s Weapon Unleash system!
